    </ul>
    <h2>Moving</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>When you run out of move speed, you can’t move at all! Your jump ends there</li>
        <li>You can long jump equal to your strength score (in feet) if you move at least 10 feet before the jump (half from a standing jump)</li>
        <li>You can high jump equal to 3’ + strength modifier if you move at least 10 feet before the high jump (half from a standing jump)</li>
        <li>You can add half your height to grab onto a ledge</li>
        <li>Swimming &amp; Climbing costs double movement</li>
        <li>Difficult terrain costs double movement (on top of existing modifiers). The cost of movement is to enter the square, not leave it. So if you have 5’ of movement left, and you want to move onto difficult terrain, you cannot do that</li>
        <li>Special movements (getting up from prone, mounting a horse etc.) consume half your move speed</li>
        <li>Skill checks can extend the distances you can jump / climb</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Bonus action</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Most class features use your bonus action</li>
        <li>When you make skill checks (intimidate, etc..) you can normally use either an action or a bonus action</li>
        <li>All bonus actions can be used as actions, but not all actions can be used as bonus actions</li>
    </ul>
