<section>
    <header>Attacking</header>
    <ul>
        <li>DC means "Difficulty Check" or the number that you need to reach to do something</li>
        <li>Advantage &amp; disadvantage cancel eachother out</li>
        <li>Resistance means takes half damage</li>
        <li>Vulnerable to means double the damage</li>
        <li>Class features may break up the standard combat loop</li>
        <li>"Flanking" means you can draw a line between your character and another character on an enemy. This gives both of you advantage on your attacks.</li>
        <li>Rolling a 1 is an automatic miss, and rolling a 20 is an automatic crit. Crit means roll double damage (so 2d8 instead of 1d8)</li>
        <li>Area of effect, see: <a href="http://rpg.stackexchange.com/questions/46492/how-do-i-map-a-15-cone-to-a-1-grid">AoE Help</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Generally, combat will go:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Declare your attack</li>
        <li>Roll to hit w/ damage dice</li>
        <li>DM will declare results</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        The below sections will further elaborate
    </p>
    <h2>Melee Combat</h2>
    <p>Melee combat is definitely the most straightforward. Walk up, declare to hit. Your formula is: <code>1d20 + profiency bonus + strength</code>. If you have a <code>Finese</code> weapon, you can add dexterity instead of strength.</p>
    <h2>Ranged Combat</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>80/320 means you can hit something 80 feet away without a penalty, 320 feet away with disadvantage</li>
        <li>Firing into melee (opponent is engaged in combat with an ally) gives you disadvantage</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Spell Combat</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Declare your spell</li>
        <ul>
            <li>Name of spell</li>
            <li>School of magic</li>
            <li>Type of spell (melee, ranged, save, other)</li>
            <li>Spell slot expended</li>
            <li>Damage done</li>
            <li>Save DCs</li>
        </ul>
        <li>Roll to hit / damage</li>
        <li>DM will declare results</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
        Spell Damage:
        <ul>
            <li>Melee spell attack (aka "Touch" attack) <code>1d20 + profiency bonus + spellcasting modifier</code> against enemy AC</li>
            <li>Ranged spell attack <code>1d20 + profiency bonus + spellcasting modifier</code> against enemy AC</li>
            <li>Save spell <code>8 + proficiency bonus + spellcasting modifier</code> against enemy save</li>
            <li>Other (typically a variant of "Save")</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
        Spellcasting modifier list:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Intelligence</strong>: Wizard</li>
            <li><strong>Charisma</strong>: Bard, Paladin, Sorcerer, Warlock</li>
            <li><strong>Wisdom</strong>: Cleric, Druid, Monk, Ranger</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/DnD/comments/2hpy09/5e_spellcasting_class_ability_reference_table/">Other</a></li>
        </ul>
    </p>
