<section>
    <header>Magic</header>
    <h2>Spellcasting Requirements - C/V/S</h2>
    <p>
        Spells ar really loud. Somatic means you need at least one hand free to cast
        Can’t make somatic gestures if your hands are bound
        Can’t make somatic gestures if you have no hands
    </p>
    <p>
        Components are normally free, assuming you have a component pouch or spellcasting focus (depending on class)
        Components that have a gold cost associated with them, e.g. holy water, are not free
        Read the spell components! They are normally funny and ironic
    </p>
    <h2>Concentration</h2>
    <p>
        You can only have one concentration spell active
        Concentration spells last until you end concentration (willingly), or the duration runs out
        If you take any damage while concentrating, you must make a con save
        DC is 10 or the half the damage, whichever is higher
    </p>
    <h2>Spells Known &amp; Spells Prepared</h2>
    <h2>Obtaining spells</h2>
    <p>
        Some castors gain new spells every time they level up, and can cast spells from this “Spell Pool” whenever they wish
        Some castors always have the same number of spells known (e.g. clerics). But every long rest they “pick” which spells they have “prepared” for that day
        Warlocks always know all of their spells, but only have a limited number of spell slots
    </p>
    <h2>Gotchyhas</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Spell level is NOT the same as character level</li>
    </ul>
